# Exercise 004 - Using string variables

1) Log into the machine with the credentials you own;

2) Touch a file called 'user_info.sh', append interpreter (shebang) at the
   beginning and make it executable. Make sure the executable bit is added;

3) Open 'user_info.sh' in your favorite editor and write a script, using BASH
   BUILTIN VARIABLES for user info and COMMAND SUBSTITUTION for the date, that
   will output like this:
   
   My username is 'INSERT_YOUR_NAME_HERE'
   My User ID is 'INSERT_YOUR_UID_HERE'
   Report done at 'INSERT_DATE_AND_TIME_HERE'

4) Execute your script;
